   NAME
	GUESSBOOTDEV - Identifes the bootable volume's name.

   FORMAT
	GUESSBOOTDEV [TO <file name>]

   TEMPLATE
	BOOTDISKNAME,TO/K

   PATH
	INSTALL3.2:C/GUESSBOOTDEV

   FUNCTION
	GUESSBOOTDEV will try to identify and display the name of the 
	volume the Amiga has booted from.

   EXAMPLES

	1> GUESSBOOTDEV
	Install3.2:

	This means that the Amiga was booted from the "Install3.2:" 
	volume.
